  "text": "Besides the NO-mediated effects, most recently proposed are NO-independent and NSAID-independent actions on NFB and MAPK/ERK signaling pathways [see [CITATION_1] ]. In their study, Idris and co [CITATION_2] reported the ability of HCT1026 to inhibit receptor activator of NFkB (RANKL), as well as RANKL-induced activation of NFkB and ERK pathway in LPS-stimulated macrophage cultures. In addition, HCT1026 also inhibited TNF-α, IL-1 and LPS-induced signaling. Interestingly enough, the pathways inhibited by HCT1026 all share a similar kinase complex upstream of the NFkB and ERK pathways and this is the most likely target for the action of HCT1026 [CITATION_3] .",
